WEBVTT

00:05.755 --> 00:08.425
(ENGINE RUMBLES)

00:08.466 --> 00:11.970
-(BIRDS SQUAWKING)
-♪ (DARING MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

00:15.640 --> 00:17.058
(CAR HORN HONKING)

00:18.685 --> 00:19.894
RICH: Come on, Lilly!

00:34.576 --> 00:36.244
-♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

00:36.286 --> 00:37.579
CLINT BOWERS:
Lilly, when we last spoke,

00:37.620 --> 00:39.622
you said you weren't quite sure
you could describe

00:39.706 --> 00:41.291
what you saw
at the theater that night.

00:41.374 --> 00:43.793
Still can't, but now
I don't have to because--

00:43.877 --> 00:45.628
'Cause we got
the pictures, Chief Bowers.

00:45.712 --> 00:47.130
We have one where
this thing looks

00:47.213 --> 00:48.631
like the monster version
of Teddy,

00:48.673 --> 00:50.675
-which was incredibly scary--
-Rich.

00:51.217 --> 00:52.343
Who is he?

00:52.427 --> 00:54.929
Ricardo Santo, sir.
But you can call me Rich.

00:56.514 --> 00:58.349
Whatever killed Teddy, Phil,
and Susie,

00:58.433 --> 01:00.769
it came after us again
last night in the cemetery.

01:00.810 --> 01:03.146
What the hell were you doing
at the cemetery at night?

01:03.229 --> 01:04.813
So, my cousin Bembe
told me this thing

01:04.855 --> 01:06.691
-my uncle used to do--
-We were just cutting through.

01:06.775 --> 01:08.902
Yeah, taking a shortcut home.

01:08.985 --> 01:10.695
And you all just happened
to have a camera with you

01:10.779 --> 01:11.821
when it did.

01:11.863 --> 01:13.239
We were ready this time.

01:14.949 --> 01:17.827
Well, let's have a look-see.

01:21.081 --> 01:22.289
Oh my God.

01:23.416 --> 01:24.501
Kirn, Wallace, look at this.

01:27.962 --> 01:29.714
Jesus H. Christ.

01:29.798 --> 01:31.591
-KIRN: What the hell is that?
-WALLACE: I don't...

01:32.133 --> 01:33.301
CLINT: Is that a...

01:34.426 --> 01:36.012
Is this pigeon shit?

01:36.054 --> 01:38.765
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

01:38.848 --> 01:40.183
LILLY BAINBRIDGE:
It's not possible.

01:40.225 --> 01:45.354
What's this? Oh, dead flowers.
Helpful. Aunt Mary's headstone.

01:45.854 --> 01:48.691
A tree. (SCOFFS)

01:48.775 --> 01:50.985
Stop, wait. Look at that one.

01:51.027 --> 01:52.904
Yeah, that's it, right there.

01:54.197 --> 01:55.865
(SIGHS)

01:55.907 --> 01:57.951
♪ (MUSIC TURNS EERIE) ♪

01:59.452 --> 02:00.995
-The statue?
-No, are you blind?

02:01.037 --> 02:02.455
It's a clown!

02:02.539 --> 02:04.415
You watch your tone, young lady.

02:04.499 --> 02:06.709
You walk into this office
telling tall tales

02:06.793 --> 02:07.961
and you show me this as proof?

02:08.044 --> 02:10.003
The only thing this is proof of
is that you, Lilly Bainbridge,

02:10.045 --> 02:11.464
are trying to buy yourself
a one-way ticket

02:11.548 --> 02:12.841
back to the nuthouse.

02:14.634 --> 02:18.346
You kids keep your noses
out of police business,

02:18.888 --> 02:21.224
or ghouls and goblins

02:21.266 --> 02:23.309
will be the very least
of your worries.

02:23.393 --> 02:25.436
Do I make myself
perfectly clear?

02:25.520 --> 02:28.314
♪ (MUSIC BUILDS) ♪

02:28.398 --> 02:29.732
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

02:29.774 --> 02:32.861
♪ ("A SMILE AND A RIBBON" BY
PATIENCE AND PRUDENCE PLAYING) ♪

02:34.904 --> 02:37.740
♪ A smile is something special ♪

02:37.781 --> 02:40.451
♪ A ribbon is something rare ♪

02:40.535 --> 02:43.413
♪ So, I'll be special
And I'll be rare ♪

02:43.454 --> 02:47.500
♪ With a smile
And a ribbon in my hair ♪

02:49.085 --> 02:51.796
♪ To be a girl they notice ♪

02:51.880 --> 02:54.632
♪ Takes more
Than a fancy dress ♪

02:54.716 --> 02:57.552
♪ So, I'll be noticed
Because I'll dress ♪

02:57.594 --> 03:02.515
♪ With a smile
And a ribbon in my tresses ♪

03:03.516 --> 03:05.935
♪ The bigger my toothy grin is ♪

03:06.019 --> 03:08.813
♪ The smaller my troubles grow ♪

03:08.897 --> 03:11.649
♪ The louder I say I'm happy ♪

03:11.733 --> 03:14.194
♪ The more I believe it so ♪

03:14.277 --> 03:17.363
♪ So, I'll have
That extra something ♪

03:17.447 --> 03:20.158
♪ 'Cause I'll know
What to wear ♪

03:20.241 --> 03:23.411
♪ So, I'll be special
And I'll be rare ♪

03:23.453 --> 03:26.289
♪ I'll be something
Beyond compare ♪

03:26.372 --> 03:27.624
♪ I'll be noticed ♪

03:27.707 --> 03:33.129
♪ Because I'll wear a smile
And a ribbon in my hair ♪

03:34.756 --> 03:37.175
♪ The bigger my toothy grin is ♪

03:37.258 --> 03:40.136
